{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You know, I am so bad at tech"},{"time":5000,"text":"that my daughter -- who is now 41 --"},{"time":7000,"text":"when she was five, was overheard by me"},{"time":10000,"text":"to say to a friend of hers,"},{"time":12000,"text":"If it doesn't bleed when you cut it,"},{"time":14000,"text":"my daddy doesn't understand it."},{"time":16000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":17000,"text":"So, the assignment I've been given \n"},{"time":19000,"text":"may be an insuperable obstacle for me,"},{"time":21000,"text":"but I'm certainly going to try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"What have I heard"},{"time":26000,"text":"during these last four days?"},{"time":29000,"text":"This is my third visit to TED."},{"time":31000,"text":"One was to TEDMED, and one, as you've heard,"},{"time":33000,"text":"was a regular TED two years ago."},{"time":35000,"text":"I've heard what I consider an extraordinary thing"},{"time":38000,"text":"that I've only heard a little bit in the two previous TEDs,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and what that is is an interweaving"},{"time":45000,"text":"and an interlarding, an intermixing,"},{"time":48000,"text":"of a sense of social responsibility"},{"time":51000,"text":"in so many of the talks --"},{"time":54000,"text":"global responsibility, in fact,"},{"time":57000,"text":"appealing to enlightened self-interest,"},{"time":61000,"text":"but it goes far beyond enlightened self-interest."},{"time":65000,"text":"One of the most impressive things"},{"time":67000,"text":"about what some, perhaps 10,"},{"time":70000,"text":"of the speakers have been talking about"},{"time":73000,"text":"is the realization, as you listen to them carefully, that they're not saying:"},{"time":76000,"text":"Well, this is what we should do; this is what I would like you to do."},{"time":79000,"text":"It's: This is what I have done"},{"time":81000,"text":"because I'm excited by it,"},{"time":83000,"text":"because it's a wonderful thing, and it's done something for me"},{"time":86000,"text":"and, of course, it's accomplished a great deal."},{"time":89000,"text":"It's the old concept, the real Greek concept,"},{"time":92000,"text":"of philanthropy in its original sense:"},{"time":96000,"text":"phil-anthropy, the love of humankind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"And the only explanation I can have"},{"time":101000,"text":"for some of what you've been hearing in the last four days"},{"time":104000,"text":"is that it arises, in fact, out of a form of love."},{"time":108000,"text":"And this gives me enormous hope."},{"time":111000,"text":"And hope, of course, is the topic"},{"time":113000,"text":"that I'm supposed to be speaking about,"},{"time":115000,"text":"which I'd completely forgotten about until I arrived."},{"time":119000,"text":"And when I did, I thought,"},{"time":121000,"text":"well, I'd better look this word up in the dictionary."},{"time":124000,"text":"So, Sarah and I -- my wife -- walked over to the public library,"},{"time":127000,"text":"which is four blocks away, on Pacific Street, and we got the OED,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and we looked in there, and there are 14 definitions of hope,"},{"time":135000,"text":"none of which really hits you"},{"time":138000,"text":"between the eyes as being the appropriate one."},{"time":141000,"text":"And, of course, that makes sense,"},{"time":143000,"text":"because hope is an abstract phenomenon; it's an abstract idea,"},{"time":146000,"text":"it's not a concrete word."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"Well, it reminds me a little bit of surgery."},{"time":152000,"text":"If there's one operation for a disease, you know it works."},{"time":156000,"text":"If there are 15 operations, you know that none of them work."},{"time":158000,"text":"And that's the way it is with definitions of words."},{"time":161000,"text":"If you have appendicitis, they take your appendix out, and you're cured."},{"time":165000,"text":"If you've got reflux oesophagitis, there are 15 procedures,"},{"time":168000,"text":"and Joe Schmo does it one way"},{"time":170000,"text":"and Will Blow does it another way,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and none of them work, and that's the way it is with this word, hope."},{"time":175000,"text":"They all come down to the idea of an expectation"},{"time":178000,"text":"of something good that is due to happen."},{"time":181000,"text":"And you know what I found out?"},{"time":183000,"text":"The Indo-European root of the word hope"},{"time":186000,"text":"is a stem, K-E-U --"},{"time":188000,"text":"we would spell it K-E-U; it's pronounced koy --"},{"time":193000,"text":"and it is the same root from which the word curve comes from."},{"time":197000,"text":"But what it means in the original Indo-European"},{"time":201000,"text":"is a change in direction, going in a different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"And I find that very interesting and very provocative,"},{"time":208000,"text":"because what you've been hearing in the last couple of days"},{"time":211000,"text":"is the sense of going in different directions:"},{"time":215000,"text":"directions that are specific and unique to problems."},{"time":218000,"text":"There are different paradigms."},{"time":220000,"text":"You've heard that word several times in the last four days,"},{"time":222000,"text":"and everyone's familiar with Kuhnian paradigms."},{"time":225000,"text":"So, when we think of hope now,"},{"time":227000,"text":"we have to think of looking in other directions"},{"time":230000,"text":"than we have been looking."},{"time":233000,"text":"There's another -- not definition, but description, of hope"},{"time":236000,"text":"that has always appealed to me, and it was one by VÃ¡clav Havel"},{"time":240000,"text":"in his perfectly spectacular book \"Breaking the Peace,\""},{"time":244000,"text":"in which he says that hope"},{"time":246000,"text":"does not consist of the expectation that things will"},{"time":249000,"text":"come out exactly right,"},{"time":251000,"text":"but the expectation that they will make sense"},{"time":254000,"text":"regardless of how they come out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"I can't tell you how reassured I was"},{"time":260000,"text":"by the very last sentence"},{"time":263000,"text":"in that glorious presentation by Dean Kamen a few days ago."},{"time":268000,"text":"I wasn't sure I heard it right,"},{"time":270000,"text":"so I found him in one of the inter-sessions."},{"time":274000,"text":"He was talking to a very large man, but I didn't care. \n"},{"time":277000,"text":"I interrupted, and I said, \"Did you say this?\""},{"time":279000,"text":"He said, \"I think so.\""},{"time":281000,"text":"So, here's what it is: I'll repeat it."},{"time":283000,"text":"\"The world will not be saved by the Internet.\""},{"time":287000,"text":"It's wonderful. Do you know what the world will be saved by?"},{"time":291000,"text":"I'll tell you. It'll be saved by the human spirit."},{"time":293000,"text":"And by the human spirit, I don't mean anything divine,"},{"time":296000,"text":"I don't mean anything supernatural --"},{"time":298000,"text":"certainly not coming from this skeptic."},{"time":302000,"text":"What I mean is this ability"},{"time":304000,"text":"that each of us has"},{"time":306000,"text":"to be something greater than herself or himself;"},{"time":312000,"text":"to arise out of our ordinary selves and achieve something"},{"time":316000,"text":"that at the beginning we thought perhaps we were not capable of."},{"time":320000,"text":"On an elemental level, we have all felt"},{"time":323000,"text":"that spirituality at the time of childbirth."},{"time":326000,"text":"Some of you have felt it in laboratories;"},{"time":328000,"text":"some of you have felt it at the workbench."},{"time":330000,"text":"We feel it at concerts."},{"time":332000,"text":"I've felt it in the operating room, at the bedside."},{"time":335000,"text":"It is an elevation of us beyond ourselves."},{"time":338000,"text":"And I think that it's going to be, in time,"},{"time":342000,"text":"the elements of the human spirit that we've been hearing about"},{"time":346000,"text":"bit by bit by bit from so many of the speakers in the last few days."},{"time":351000,"text":"And if there's anything that has permeated this room,"},{"time":355000,"text":"it is precisely that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"I'm intrigued by"},{"time":361000,"text":"a concept that was brought to life"},{"time":364000,"text":"in the early part of the 19th century --"},{"time":366000,"text":"actually, in the second decade of the 19th century --"},{"time":370000,"text":"by a 27-year-old poet"},{"time":373000,"text":"whose name was Percy Shelley."},{"time":375000,"text":"Now, we all think that Shelley"},{"time":377000,"text":"obviously is the great romantic poet that he was; \n"},{"time":380000,"text":"many of us tend to forget that he wrote"},{"time":385000,"text":"some perfectly wonderful essays, too,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and the most well-remembered essay"},{"time":391000,"text":"is one called \"A Defence of Poetry.\""},{"time":395000,"text":"Now, it's about five, six, seven, eight pages long,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and it gets kind of deep and difficult after about the third page,"},{"time":401000,"text":"but somewhere on the second page"},{"time":405000,"text":"he begins talking about the notion"},{"time":409000,"text":"that he calls \"moral imagination.\""},{"time":414000,"text":"And here's what he says, roughly translated:"},{"time":419000,"text":"A man -- generic man --"},{"time":423000,"text":"a man, to be greatly good,"},{"time":426000,"text":"must imagine clearly."},{"time":429000,"text":"He must see himself and the world"},{"time":434000,"text":"through the eyes of another,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and of many others."},{"time":442000,"text":"See himself and the world -- not just the world, but see himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"What is it that is expected of us"},{"time":451000,"text":"by the billions of people"},{"time":454000,"text":"who live in what Laurie Garrett the other day"},{"time":457000,"text":"so appropriately called"},{"time":459000,"text":"despair and disparity?"},{"time":461000,"text":"What is it that they have every right"},{"time":465000,"text":"to ask of us?"},{"time":467000,"text":"What is it that we have every right to ask of ourselves,"},{"time":471000,"text":"out of our shared humanity and out of the human spirit?"},{"time":476000,"text":"Well, you know precisely what it is."},{"time":479000,"text":"There's a great deal of argument"},{"time":481000,"text":"about whether we, as the great nation that we are,"},{"time":485000,"text":"should be the policeman of the world,"},{"time":488000,"text":"the world's constabulary,"},{"time":491000,"text":"but there should be virtually no argument"},{"time":495000,"text":"about whether we should be the world's healer."},{"time":500000,"text":"There has certainly been no argument about that"},{"time":503000,"text":"in this room in the past four days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"So, if we are to be the world's healer,"},{"time":510000,"text":"every disadvantaged person in this world --"},{"time":513000,"text":"including in the United States -- becomes our patient."},{"time":518000,"text":"Every disadvantaged nation, and perhaps our own nation,"},{"time":522000,"text":"becomes our patient."},{"time":525000,"text":"So, it's fun to think about the etymology of the word \"patient.\""},{"time":530000,"text":"It comes initially from the Latin patior, to endure, or to suffer."},{"time":539000,"text":"So, you go back to the old Indo-European root again,"},{"time":542000,"text":"and what do you find? The Indo-European stem is pronounced payen --"},{"time":546000,"text":"we would spell it P-A-E-N -- and, lo and behold, mirabile dictu,"},{"time":551000,"text":"it is the same root as the word compassion comes from, P-A-E-N."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"So, the lesson is very clear. The lesson is that our patient --"},{"time":562000,"text":"the world, and the disadvantaged of the world --"},{"time":566000,"text":"that patient deserves our compassion."},{"time":571000,"text":"But beyond our compassion, and far greater than compassion,"},{"time":574000,"text":"is our moral imagination"},{"time":576000,"text":"and our identification with each individual"},{"time":580000,"text":"who lives in that world,"},{"time":583000,"text":"not to think of them as a huge forest,"},{"time":587000,"text":"but as individual trees."},{"time":590000,"text":"Of course, in this day and age, the trick is not to let each tree"},{"time":594000,"text":"be obscured by that Bush in Washington that can get --"},{"time":598000,"text":"can get in the way."},{"time":600000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":602000,"text":"So, here we are."},{"time":604000,"text":"We are, should be,"},{"time":607000,"text":"morally committed to"},{"time":610000,"text":"being the healer of the world."},{"time":614000,"text":"And we have had examples over and over and over again --"},{"time":618000,"text":"you've just heard one in the last 15 minutes --"},{"time":622000,"text":"of people who have not only had that commitment,"},{"time":626000,"text":"but had the charisma, the brilliance --"},{"time":628000,"text":"and I think in this room it's easy to use the word brilliant, my God --"},{"time":632000,"text":"the brilliance to succeed at least at the beginning"},{"time":636000,"text":"of their quest,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and who no doubt will continue to succeed,"},{"time":641000,"text":"as long as more and more of us enlist ourselves in their cause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"Now, if we're talking"},{"time":649000,"text":"about medicine,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and we're talking about healing,"},{"time":654000,"text":"I'd like to quote someone who hasn't been quoted."},{"time":658000,"text":"It seems to me everybody in the world's been quoted here:"},{"time":660000,"text":"Pogo's been quoted;"},{"time":662000,"text":"Shakespeare's been quoted backwards, forwards, inside out."},{"time":666000,"text":"I would like to quote one of my own household gods."},{"time":669000,"text":"I suspect he never really said this,"},{"time":672000,"text":"because we don't know what Hippocrates really said,"},{"time":675000,"text":"but we do know for sure that one of the great Greek physicians"},{"time":678000,"text":"said the following,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and it has been recorded in one of the books attributed to Hippocrates,"},{"time":684000,"text":"and the book is called \"Precepts.\""},{"time":686000,"text":"And I'll read you what it is."},{"time":689000,"text":"Remember, I have been talking about,"},{"time":692000,"text":"essentially philanthropy:"},{"time":694000,"text":"the love of humankind, the individual humankind"},{"time":699000,"text":"and the individual humankind \n"},{"time":701000,"text":"that can bring that kind of love"},{"time":703000,"text":"translated into action,"},{"time":706000,"text":"translated, in some cases, into enlightened self-interest."},{"time":709000,"text":"And here he is, 2,400 years ago:"},{"time":714000,"text":"\"Where there is love of humankind,"},{"time":718000,"text":"there is love of healing.\""},{"time":721000,"text":"We have seen that here today"},{"time":724000,"text":"with the sense,"},{"time":726000,"text":"with the sensitivity --"},{"time":729000,"text":"and in the last three days,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and with the power of the indomitable human spirit."},{"time":735000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":737000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}